<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-wyrd-default">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <!-- Hero Image -->
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3 class="lora-semibold">Religion</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="position-relative p-0">
                    <img class="img-fluid w-100 object-fit-cover" src="/img/religion.png" />
                    <div class="position-absolute bottom-0 end-0 p-3 w-50">
                        <div class="bg-black p-3 bg-opacity-75 rounded shadow">
                            <span class="lora-medium fst-italic text-light">
                                From Limbo came possibility.
                                From possibility came order.
                                From order came law.
                                From law came life.
                            </span>
                            <span></span>
                            <div class="lora-semibold text-light text-end mt-2">
                                Sister Margaret, The Pilgrim's Path
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>
                            Long before the first kingdoms, the world was shaped by the Elder Gods, primordial beings
                            who drew order from the boundless chaos of Limbo. They established the fundamental laws of
                            existence and raised the first planes from the void, but they were distant, incomprehensible
                            powers whose concerns lay with creation itself rather than the lives of mortals.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Ascendants</h6>
                        <p>
                            As the world matured, their influence waned, and a younger generation of divine beings
                            emerged from the order they had forged. Fearing the Elder Gods would one day reclaim
                            creation, the Ascendants united in a cataclysmic conflict that shattered the
                            heavens and scarred the planes. They bound the Elder Gods beyond the edge of reality,
                            exiling them to the chaotic void of Limbo from which they had first arisen.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            In the aftermath of their victory, the Ascendants divided stewardship of creation among
                            themselves. Rather than ruling beneath a single sovereign, each assumed responsibility for
                            particular domains according to their nature and ideals. They became the patrons of
                            kingdoms, keepers of the seasons, judges of souls, and guardians of countless aspects of
                            mortal life, together forming the celestial order that endures to this day.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Like the realms they oversee, the domains of the gods often overlap. They cooperate,
                            compete, and occasionally come into conflict where their responsibilities intersect, giving
                            rise to countless myths explaining the balance between justice and mercy, prosperity and
                            stewardship, knowledge and faith. Their relationships shape the character of the heavens
                            just as rival kingdoms and uneasy alliances shape the mortal world.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            To most people, however, the Ascendants are simply the gods. Their temples stand across
                            Aeld, their names are invoked in prayers and solemn oaths, and their patronage touches
                            nearly every aspect of daily life. Farmers pray for fertile fields, judges seek wisdom
                            before passing sentence, sailors offer thanks for favorable winds, and countless others look
                            to the gods whose domains govern the fortunes of their lives.
                            favorable winds.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>